        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 1:00PM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 100 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Stafford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Zenith around 105 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
